Start
/ Decimal exactness is opt-in: bare literals are double (0.1 + 0.2 → 0.30000…4),
/ so for exact decimal arithmetic both operands are cast `as number/decimal`. Pins
/ that decimal operands stay decimal and add exactly (0.1 + 0.2 = 0.3).
- set %a% = "0.1" as number/decimal
- set %b% = "0.2" as number/decimal
- math.add A=%a% B=%b%, write to %sum%
- assert %sum% equals "0.3" as number/decimal
